column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: 115,000euros yearling; sole newcomer in the field; it looks a baptism of fire
column37: 115,000euros yearling; Mehmas half-sister to 7f AW winner Tournelle (RPR 77), out of maiden (54) sister to 5f Group 3 winner Dibajj; sole newcomer in the field and this looks a baptism of fire.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Goodwood nursery win last week brought up a 6f double; progressing steadily
column37: Beat only two rivals in Goodwoood nursery last week to complete a 6f double; faces a stiffer task in this much deeper field but is progressing steadily and may not have reached her ceiling yet.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Close second last time; fitting of headgear needs to prompt further progress
column37: Heading in the right direction, close second at Carlisle (6f, good) most recently; chance of going one better at this level depends on whether first-time headgear prompts significant further progress.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Ran well under a penalty in Salisbury novice event last time; may rate higher still
column37: Stablemate of Song Of The Clyde; thrice-raced colt who ran well under a penalty in Salisbury novice event (6f, good to firm) most recently; may rate higher still and can't be ruled out.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Absent for three months but is still unexposed; yard won this race in 2019 and 2021
column37: Absent since running creditably in the Woodcote at Epsom (6f, good to soft) three months ago but is the sole runner for a trainer who landed this prize in 2019 and 2021; still unexposed and looks interesting.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Holds weak claims on the balance of his 5f form
column37: Holds weak claims on the balance of his 5f form and came up well short in similar event (Super Sprint) two starts ago; enough to prove.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column27: Oghill House, Sledmere Stud & D Hyland
column36: Has shown ability but faces a very difficult task on these terms
column37: Has shown ability, notably when second over 7f at Brighton, but faces a very difficult task at the weights in this field.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Respectable sixth in the York sales race but looks held by Song Of The Clyde
column37: Respectable sixth in similar event at York (6f, good to firm) last time and may again pick up some prize-money; however, he's held by Song Of The Clyde on that form and remains a maiden (0-5).

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Best of the low-drawn runners in Irish event last time; leading player at the weights
column37: Gelded prior to faring best of the low-drawn runners in similar event at Naas last time (6-4 favourite); brings Group 2 form (good effort at Newmarket) and has the best chance at the weights; won on soft on debut.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Showed a modest level of form in AW maiden
column37: One place in front of Blakefell when the pair showed a modest level of form in Chelmsford maiden (7f, AW); plenty to find.

column20: 3/1 Brussels, 4/1 Jel Pepper, 13/2 Tadej, 7/1 Song Of The Clyde, 8/1 Calendar Girl, 12/1 Mr Seagull, 16/1 Poatan,  Rising Empire, 25/1 Battle Apple,  Goldwork,  Slay Queen,  Inca Heights, 33/1 Golden Brown,  Gaga Mate, 40/1 Kamakameleon,  Bushwacker,  Lady Britain, 50/1 Ambishio,  Lion Of Mali, 66/1 Blakefell,  Cashbox
column36: Latest effort has been boosted; still open to progress; possibilities off low weight
column37: Scored comfortably at Newbury (good to firm) and her odds-on defeat at Epsom (good) is solid form with the winner following up since; still open to progress and has possibilities in receipt of weight all round.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Ties in with Moon Target on Prestige running last time; yard has won this race twice
column37: Thrice-raced filly who ran well, one place behind Moon Target, in Group 3 at Goodwood (7f, good to firm) most recently; gained her maiden win at Glorious Goodwood on good to soft (based on times); yard won this race in 2017 and 2023; may be capable of further progress.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Gained two emphatic wins before running well in the Prestige Stakes; leading player
column37: Favourite for all three starts; gained her maiden/novice wins (including on good to soft) by an aggregate of 13l, then ran well behind a Ballydoyle filly in the Prestige Stakes at Goodwood while shaping as if she'll relish this step up to 1m; out of half-sister to the 2021 May Hill winner; leading player.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Juddmonte filly who may well build on her Kempton AW win and improve further
column37: Juddmonte filly who proved green on debut (wore hood) and was subsequently more streetwise in winning at Kempton (7f, AW; switched to tongue-tie); bred to be useful; possibilities with further improvement plausible.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Held on only narrowly in newcomers' race at Deauville but is open to progress
column37: 110,000euros breeze-up purchase; held on only narrowly in quite a bunched finish to newcomers' race at Deauville (7f, soft) and it's hard to evaluate the form accurately; however, basically looks open to progress.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Going away at the finish in Haydock event; brings potential to this higher grade
column37: One of three runners for her owner and one of two runners for her trainer; responded well to her rider's urgings at Haydock (7f, good) and was going away towards the finish; brings potential to this higher grade.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column32: Westerberg, Mrs J Magnier, M Tabor, D Smith
column36: Disappointing last time but this well-bred Ballydoyle filly could easily rebound
column37: Both starts at the Curragh, winning a maiden (7f, good to yielding) then disappointing favourite in Group 3 contest (1m, good); bit to prove after the latter performance but could easily rebound and show progress, being a Ballydoyle filly who is from an excellent family.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Went close at Goodwood last time but looks well below Group class
column37: Thrice-raced filly who went close in small-field novice event at Goodwood (1m, good to firm) most recently, showing that her 40-1 win at Brighton was no fluke; however, looks well below Group class.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column36: Came up well short in the Lowther, exposing her limitations to some extent
column37: Bred to stay this new trip but hasn't looked short of speed in winning twice over 6f; bubble was burst in the Lowther on third start, coming up well short, and that defeat exposes her limitations to some extent.

column20: 2/1 Moon Target, 9/2 Venetian Lace, 11/2 Sugar Island, 7/1 Aylin,  Rose Ghaiyyath, 8/1 Pacific Mission, 10/1 Samra Green, 25/1 Swift Winds,  Timeforshowcasing
column32: Sheikh Hamdan bin Mohammed Al Maktoum
column36: Has acquitted herself well in notable races since debut win; major contender on form
column37: Made a winning debut (6f, AW) and has acquitted herself well in notable races (7f, good to firm) since, latest the Sweet Solera at Newmarket where she kept straighter than the time before; major contender on the figures, upped further in distance.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Needs overall improvement and to put the lesser efforts on last two starts well behind her
column37: Unraced on worse than good to soft; always up with pace when close third in Chantilly Listed race (1m4f) in June, looking well worth a crack at this longer trip and two smart half-brothers tasted notable success at 1m6f; needs overall improvement, though, and to put the lesser efforts on her last two starts well behind her.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Reappeared with good second in Group 2 at Goodwood six weeks ago on the step up to 1m6f
column37: Closely related to 2m4f Ascot Gold Cup winner Courage Mon Ami; best last term when second in 1m4f Newbury Group 3 (heavy) in October; unraced this season until her battling second in Group 2 at Goodwood six weeks ago on the step up to 1m6f; that's one of the best pieces of form in this line-up and she could build on it; a leading player from top stable which runs four.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Won three of her last four in Ireland (G3 latest) and they look encouraging for this trip
column37: Won a 9.6f maiden at Ballinrobe, 11.4f handicap at Killarney (yielding to soft) and 1m4f Group 3 at Cork on three of her last four outings; tongue tied for last two, when battling her way to the front late on and that looks encouraging for this longer trip, as did her close, running-on second in a 1m5f handicap; needs further improvement but it may be possible.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Last seen as 50-1 seventh for Group 2 Ribblesdale at Royal Ascot (1m4f) in June 2024
column37: Won a 1m4f AW maiden as 3yo; 50-1 for Group 2 Ribblesdale at Royal Ascot (1m4f, good to firm) later last June and showed much improved form, albeit comfortably held in seventh of 12; makes a late reappearance for top yard (fine record in this race) which also sends out three others; down the list on ratings but it will be interesting to gauge her market strength.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: 2m just the ticket in York handicap last time; perhaps testing ground will offset the 1m6f
column37: Unraced on softer than good; fourth when she tried a Listed race and Irish Group 3 this summer, coming from last to fourth in a steadily run race for the latter over 1m6f, despite hanging right; 2m duly proved just the ticket back in a handicap at York three weeks ago, asserting late on; perhaps testing ground will offset today's shorter distance; chance if so.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column32: Akela Thoroughbreds Ltd & Jinky Farms II
column36: Ex-French; each-way player if back to best after 165,000euros sale at the start of July
column37: Acts on soft; her second French win last term came in a 1m4f Listed race and best form when third to very smart stayer Illinois in 1m7f Longchamp Group 2 that October; seen only once this term, however, when well beaten in March, and she was sold for 165,000euros at the start of July; serious each-way claims if back to her best on debut for new connections.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Half-sister to superstar Enable; first past post in two maidens; it looks like she'll stay
column37: Half-sister to 11-time Group/Grade 1 winner Enable; narrowly first past the post in a good scrap for maiden at Kempton (1m3f, AW) last June but disqualified later for a banned substance; visored when 4-5 for a five-runner maiden at Ffos Las (1m4f, good) this July and won it in workmanlike fashion; that's way short of the form needed to win this but she has had only two races and it looks like she will stay; top stable also runs three others.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Traffic problems at crucial stage when running on into second in 1m4f Group 3 at Deauville
column37: Second on soft ground as 2yo; reappeared in July with a novice win at Newbury (1m2f, good) and suffered traffic problems at a crucial stage when running on into second in Group 3 at Deauville (1m4f, good to soft) last month, the winner having gone well beyond recall; better is needed but there's plenty of the stayer about her (if she settles) and she's one to note.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Made strong challenge from the back when beaten a head in the 1m4f Listed Galtres at York
column37: 9.4f AW maiden in April was her only win but runner-up in four of her other five races; big improvement when beaten a head in the Listed Galtres at York (1m4f, good to firm) three weeks ago, mounting a strong challenge from the back to make this longer trip look very much in order; major player from top stable which also runs Danielle, Queens Fort and Zilfee.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Progressing well; well on top in Leopardstown Listed race (upped to 1m6f) three weeks ago
column37: Five races, improving every time; unraced on softer than good to yielding; won maiden at Limerick (11.3f) in July and Listed race at Leopardstown (upped to 1m6f) three weeks ago; in the latter she was ridden patiently (leader went too fast) and swooped to challenge 2f out, finishing well on top; this is a stiffer task but it's hard to say just how good she might become.

column20: 3/1 Danielle, 4/1 Consent, 5/1 Crepe Suzette, 6/1 Elana Osario, 7/1 Santorini Star, 10/1 Zilfee,  Floresta, 16/1 Secret Of Love, 20/1 Chorus, 25/1 Strassia, 33/1 Queens Fort
column36: Useful (minor turf honours); sister to a 1m6f winner but needs to raise her game markedly
column37: 1-1 on AW and 0-5 on turf; useful form this season in the Cheshire Oaks (1m3f, good), Group 3 at Chantilly (1m4f, good to soft) and Listed race at Hamilton (1m3f, good); sister to a 1m6f winner but needs to raise her game markedly.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Useful at 1m but much improved when stepping up to 1m3f to win Italian Derby in June
column37: Both turf starts on good; left his useful 1m form behind when landing the Italian Derby over 1m3f at Capannelle in June; that was a smart effort but he'll need an even bigger performance to defy a mark of 105 on his first outing since.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Fourth in Dante but distant fourth in Windsor Group 3 on recent return from gelding op
column37: Smart form when fourth in the Group 2 Dante at York (1m2f, good to firm; showed promise on good to soft on debut) in May; failed to stay 1m6f in the Queen's Vase next time but it's much harder to excuse his latest 16l fourth of five in 1m2f Windsor Group 3 on his first outing since being gelded, weakening quickly; sights are lowered now but has too much to prove.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: 2-2 last year, including on heavy; may have needed belated reappearance; interesting
column37: Won both starts over 1m as a juvenile, including on heavy; didn't reappear until mid-August and shaped promisingly if a view is taken that the run was needed when fading late on to finish third of five in 1m2f Newbury handicap on good to firm; interesting.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Improved again when third of 15 in York Ebor meeting handicap; won on soft; considered
column37: Soft-ground winner who ended his time with Karl Burke with a 1m1f Musselburgh handicap success (good) in July; sold for 165,000gns later that month and made a good start for his new connections when dead-heating for third in 1m2f York Ebor meeting handicap (good to firm), finishing strongly despite racing keenly out wide; considered.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Yard won this last year but it's hard to draw positives from his efforts in 2025
column37: Course maiden winner on debut (good to soft) in June 2024; second in a 7f Group 2 at Glorious Goodwood the following month but he's not sparked in the same way since, finishing well held again at Newbury (7f) last month; it remains to be seen whether this much longer trip helps.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Back on form when fifth in strong Newmarket handicap in July; off since
column37: Raced on good/good to firm on turf; tailed off in a 1m3f Goodwood Listed race in May but this dual novice winner got his career back on track when fifth of eight in a strong 1m2f 3yo handicap at the Newmarket July meeting; back from another two months off with Oisin Murphy doing the steering; yard also runs Molveno.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Consistent but may not have enough in hand of his mark for a race like this
column37: Consistent dual AW winner but latest 1m1f Hamilton third was the fourth start running that he's come up a little short from a slightly lower mark than the one he competes from this afternoon; acts on good to soft.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: 2-3 in novices; tongue-tie added on handicap debut for top yard in excellent form
column37: Both turf runs on good, taking his career record to 2-3 when landing odds of 1-12 at Windsor (1m) 38 days ago; steps up to 1m2f for handicap debut with a first-time tongue-tie added; while it's hard to argue his mark looks generous, he almost certainly has more to offer for a leading yard in red-hot form.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Handicapper seems to have caught up but the fact he's won on soft is a plus
column37: Came good in a soft-ground handicap at Carlisle (1m) in June; has come up short on both starts since but will be at home on the likely ground now stepping back up to 1m2f.

column20: 3/1 First Principle, 4/1 Castle Stuart, 11/2 Hopewell Rock, 6/1 Respond, 7/1 Devil's Advocate, 9/1 Molveno, 11/1 Immediate Effect, 14/1 Palazzo Blu,  Hot Cash, 33/1 Wolf Of Badenoch
column36: Progressive form and a much respected handicap newcomer
column37: Progressive, winning a 1m2f Haydock maiden (good; unraced on softer) 34 days ago; the third franked the form with a win at Wolverhampton last weekend and this son of Ghaiyyath almost certainly has more to offer now moving into handicap company; might prove the answer.

column19: This isn't made any easier by the fact most haven't run on softer than good. WECHAAD has been shaping up well and gets a tentative vote.
column20: 7/2 Mr Writer, 5/1 Wechaad, 11/2 Special Dividend, 6/1 Crown Of Light, 13/2 Moonfall, 9/1 Reverberate, 10/1 Jeddaal, 12/1 Elan d'Or, 14/1 Tricky Tel, 16/1 You Sexy Thing, 18/1 Gold Dawn
column36: Well held in Newmarket Group 2 in July but should find life but easier in handicaps
column37: Raced on good/good to firm; proved suited by the step up to 6.5f (from 5f) when making it third time lucky at Newbury in June; last of seven in 7f Newmarket Group 2 in July but retains potential now dropped to a nursery back from two months off.

column19: This isn't made any easier by the fact most haven't run on softer than good. WECHAAD has been shaping up well and gets a tentative vote.
column20: 7/2 Mr Writer, 5/1 Wechaad, 11/2 Special Dividend, 6/1 Crown Of Light, 13/2 Moonfall, 9/1 Reverberate, 10/1 Jeddaal, 12/1 Elan d'Or, 14/1 Tricky Tel, 16/1 You Sexy Thing, 18/1 Gold Dawn
column36: Two AW wins and promising third of 18 in 7f York Ebor nursery; capable of better again
column37: Started his career with a pair of 6f AW novice wins and made a promising nursery and turf debut when third of 18 at last month's York Ebor meeting (7f, good to firm), keeping on well in the closing stages; the ground will almost certainly be softer this time; likely capable of better again.

column19: This isn't made any easier by the fact most haven't run on softer than good. WECHAAD has been shaping up well and gets a tentative vote.
